<db:section xml:id="property-documentation">
<db:title>Property Documentation</db:title>
<db:section xml:id="radius-prop">
<db:title>radius : real</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>real</db:type>
<db:varname>radius</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>This property holds the radius of the button.</db:para>
<db:para>To create a relatively square button that has slightly rounded corners, use a small value, such as <db:code>3</db:code>.</db:para>
<db:para>To create a completely circular button (the default), use a value that is equal to half of the width or height of the button, and make the button's width and height identical.</db:para>
<db:para>To reset this property back to the default value, set its value to <db:code>undefined</db:code>.</db:para>
</db:section>
